<p>Adding an asset</p><p>Add CMS content so that you can link it to work packages,
	 features, or change drivers. 
  </p> 
	  
		<ul> 
		   
			  A CMS connection is required. 
			  
		   
		 
	 </ul> 
	  
		<p>If you are going to link a work
		  package, feature, or change driver to CMS content, then the content must first
		  be added as an asset to CORDAP. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		   
			 <p>Adding deliverables as assets
				and linking them to work packages gives you the ability to track the progress
				on each individual deliverable. Using filters in the Work Packages tab, you can
				easily identify work packages linked to a deliverable. 
			 </p> 
		   
		</p>  
		 
		   In 
			 My Products, expand the desired product. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click the desired release. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Assets. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Select content. 
		   
		  CORDAP connects to the CMS connection and displays the CMS
			 content folders. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Scroll through the list of content and select the content you want
			 to add to CORDAP. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Save. 
		   
		 
	  
	  
		<p> The CMS content is added as an
		  asset and is available for linking to work packages, features, or change
		  drivers. 
		</p> 
	  
  